      • txLevel

        public int txLevel
        NUR module transmission level attenuation in dB steps.

        TX level value is attenuation from maximum level: TX level(dBm) = (MAX_TXLEVEL - txLevel) dBm.

        The transmission level range may differ depending device in use.

        Max 500mW devices range is usually 0-19.

        Max 1000mW devices (NUR2) range is usually 0-29.

        Use getDeviceCaps() to find out device capabilities to set correct transmission level.

        See Also:
        NurApi.getDeviceCaps(), NurRespDevCaps.maxTxmW, NurRespDevCaps.maxTxdBm, NurRespDevCaps.txAttnStep, NurRespDevCaps.txSteps,

        500mW reader values:

        • 0 = 27 dBm, 500mW
        • 1 = 26 dBm, 398mW
        • 2 = 25 dBm, 316mW
        • 3 = 24 dBm, 251mW
        • 4 = 23 dBm, 200mW
        • 5 = 22 dBm, 158mW
